="" width="500" height="500" natural-width="500" natural-height="500" data-lg-size="3000x3000" loading="lazy"></a></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1694166909876" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1694166909876"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><a href="/collections/refillable-notebooks" class="">Refillable Notebooks</a></p></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-3 gf_col-md-3 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1679580860705" data-id="1679580860705"></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1694100664487" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1694100664487"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1680594068342" data-id="1680594068342"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1736859322951" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1736859322951"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">All Things paper</h2><div>&nbsp;</div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1694100664486" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1694100664486"><div class="elm text-edit gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000" face="Open Sans, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">We have some nice leather covers, to hold multiple notebooks, to give the simplest books a bit more style and class, and to last a lifetime. TRAVELER'S COMPANY make the classic leather covers, and a huge selection of refills to fit.</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; text-align: inherit !important;"><br></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000" face="Open Sans, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">While a hard cover will tend to protect your notes better, and can be easier if you need the cover to support your writing; soft covers have more flex, so can be easier to fit in a pocket or bag.</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; text-align: inherit !important;"><br></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000" face="Open Sans, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">There are often choices of page layouts. For most people, lined is the classic and most commonly used. Squared, or graph paper, is a popular alternative, and dot-grid is perfect for many people, and increasingly popular. Many people find the dots give them just enough guidance, while getting in their way less than lines or squares. And, of course, there are plenty of notebooks with plain paper if you don't need the guidance at all!</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; text-align: inherit !important;"><br></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000" face="Open Sans, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">You can narrow down this list with the filters (don't forget the 'More filters' link!) or for quick access, filter the sizes with the quick links. The main A-sizes are the commonly-used sizes around most of the world, while 90x140 is a popular size for pocket notebooks, as used by Moleskine and many others, also known as 3.5"x5.5" in the USA. B-sizes fit between the A-sizes for more options.</font></p></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><script>window.__gemStoreData = {};window.__gemStoreData.gemKeyValid = {};window.__gemStoreData.gemKeyValid.bestWayAddToCart = 1;</script></div><div id="divContentBk"></div><!--End_Gem_Page_Main_Editor-->
